com.ipt.ebsa.manage.util

Class VersionCompare

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ipt.ebsa.manage.util.VersionCompare
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String>

    public class VersionCompare
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String>
    Compares two version strings. Algorithm inspired by https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/Main/RPMAndDebVersioning Breaks strings into portions defined by dots and a single dash (the last one) e.g. (xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx-xxx) Compares strings in xx.xx.xx.xx-xx format where the number of x.x's can be anything and the contents of each xx group is compared numerically if they are numbers and alphanumerically if they contain non numeric characters. if all the n.n.n's are the same then it compares the release versions (the bit after the last dash) if there are any. The release versions are compared the same way as the other strings
